File: The Formula One logo. AFP/Mark Thompson JOHANNESBURG - South Africans’ hopes of hosting the Formula 1 continue to grow and now a new piece of information has come to light. Multiple reports suggest F1 boss Stefano Domenicali is flying in to discuss the possibility of a Grand Prix in South Africa as soon as next year. READ: Verstappen calls for F1 race in Africa There've been numerous reports of the race returning to this country for the first time since 1993. The New York Times has reported that F1 could return to Kyalami in Johannesburg soon. READ: Former F1 team boss calls for SA Grand Prix Domenicali recently confirmed that South Africa is the "most likely" new venue for F1, and he he hopes it will happen "as soon as possible". Mercedes driver Lewis Hamilton and rival Red Bull driver Max Verstappen have also said they would like the race to come to Africa.